This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
2:48 PM Defendant Dieter Wilke Johnson Soetebier in court, in custody. Attorney Breanna A. Halyburton in court for Dieter Wilke Johnson Soetebier. Prosecuting attorney Mary M Sowinski in court for the State of Wisconsin. State calls Rhinelander Police Detective Sergeant Kyle M. Parish/sworn/direct by Sowinski/witness identifies Defendant/continued direct by Sowinski/cross by Halyburton/witness is excused. Halyburton statement to probable cause. Court finds probable cause exists and bind Defendant over. Sowinski states Information will be filed that mirrors Complaint. Halyburton willing to proceed to Arraignment today; waives further reading and enters not guilty pleas. Sowinski states has complied with victim rights. Bond continued. adj. 03:08 PM
Pre-trial conference scheduled for December 13, 2022 at 02:30 pm.
Defendant was transported on  writ and appeared via video- Dispatch not advised when brought on writ.  Confirmed with Brandi to cancel

1:28 PM Defendant Dieter Wilke Johnson Soetebier appeared by video, in custody. Prosecuting attorney Michael William Schiek in court for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney Elizageth Svehlek appearing specially for Breanna A. Halyburton in court for Dieter Wilke Johnson Soetebier. Motion filed to dismiss criminal complaint. Svehlek would like motion heard. Schiek statement to motion - believes there is probable cause. Svehlek stands on motion. Court statement to law - statement to complaint - denies motion. Svehlek does not know Vilas County Charges. Defendant states has not been to initial appearance in 1st case and has a $250 cash bond - has Lincoln County case that Jury Trial has not be heard yet - would like to stay in jail. Schiek/Svehlek statement to bond. Court to set for preliminary hearing. Court sets bond. adj. 01:40 PM
Preliminary hearing scheduled for October 7, 2022 at 02:45 pm.
